choices.text: the withdrawal of Soviet Union that led to great changes. The political vacuum and ideological crisis that preceded it was succeeded by total destabilization and corruption with strong growth of authoritarianism in return. During this process civil rights were violated and serious volume of human rights subject to terror. Media and businesses were the priority targets. And many who lost and were driven out of their calm life suffered and died in prisons. Kyrgyzstan realized rapid instability and became subject to external regional influences along with corrupting influences. The key shift and turn of trends came in end of 2005. External geopolitical and energy interests were the main components of the shift as they formed the framework of new power struggles Now key questions are related to Kyrgyzstan, including its stabilizer role in the region. Relying on the resources to reduce energy dependence and set new factors into play, access to the East is getting acute necessity. These facts, however, are not analyzed in the analysis and open discussions. Extensive sluiced uranium and rare materials resources of Kyrgyzstan are used for the needs of regional and international industries irrespective of economic spurs and urgent challenges of Kyrgyzstan. In addition, free access to mineral fields in Kyrgyzstan, which is not under current policy. Overall, Kyrgyz Republic needs foreign policy in order to realize its sovereignty and independence developed through difficult changes of the country. The new reality poses strategic dilemma and its coherent formulas are needed in need of critical assessment of internal and external trends. Para
